\par \pard\plain \s1\rtlch\af14\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af8\loch\keep\sb480\sa0\keepn\cf17\f8\fs32\b\dbch\af10{\loch
1. What TLO Inventory does}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80{\loch
TLO Inventory provides full inventory, incremental Add Shows processing, audio tagging, inventory searching, and artist-database searching. The source bundle contains the application sources and build utilities. The separate distribution ZIP contains native end-user applications for Windows, macOS, and generic Linux. The generic Linux applications are also used when running under WSL; there is no separate WSL application directory or WSL build.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80{\loch
The full inventory function scans configured music roots, identifies core show metadata, prepares searchable setlist text, and builds the inventory output used by the included search tools.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
Full Inventory scans configured music roots and rebuilds the inventory outputs.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
Add Shows adds new content to an existing inventory without rerunning the full scan.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
Tag and Tag During Inventory write audio file metadata when you choose to tag files.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
The included Search app searches the completed bootlist and setlist files after the distribution is extracted into TLOHome.}
\par \pard\plain \s1\rtlch\af14\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af8\loch\keep\sb480\sa0\keepn\cf17\f8\fs32\b\dbch\af10{\loch
2. Installation package and TLOHome layout}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80{\loch
Each update has a source bundle and a separate end-user distribution ZIP named TLO_V1.0BuildXXX.zip, where XXX is the bundle number. Extract the distribution ZIP so that its contents become the TLOHome folder, or extract into an existing TLOHome folder after reviewing overwrite prompts. The ZIP does not contain a versioned wrapper directory.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033{\loch
The source bundle contains the current requirements DOCX and the current RTF user manual. The distribution ZIP includes the current RTF user manual, release information, checksums, and malware-scan receipts. The requirements document remains with the source bundle and is not included in the end-user distribution ZIP.}
\par \pard\plain \s81\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af9\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\li360\lin360\ri144\rin144\sb40\sa80\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f9\fs17\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af13\langfe1033\sb60\sa120{\loch
TLOHome/\line   apps/\line     Windows/\line       tlo-ggi.exe\line       tlo-gi.exe\line       tlo-tag.exe\line       tlo-gsi.exe\line       search-artist-db.exe\line     macOS/\line       tlo-ggi\line       tlo-gi\line       tlo-tag\line       tlo-gsi\line       search-artist-db\line     Linux/\line       tlo-ggi\line       tlo-gi\line       tlo-tag\line       tlo-gsi\line       search-artist-db\line   TLO_DBs/\line     README.txt             databases are populated separately\line   debug/ dups/ logs/ readyforXfer/ setlists/ staged/\line   README_FIRST.txt\line   toBeInventoried.txt\line   checksums.txt\line   scan-reports/}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033{\loch
The distribution includes tlo-gsi and search-artist-db for Windows, macOS, and generic Linux. The generic Linux applications are also used under WSL. TLOHome/TLO_DBs is intentionally not populated by the distribution; place the separately supplied database/support files there before using database-dependent functions.}
\par \trowd\trqc\ltrrow\trkeep\trpaddft3\trpaddt0\trpaddfl3\trpaddl0\trpaddfb3\trpaddb0\trpaddfr3\trpaddr0\clpadft3\clpadt108\clpadfr3\clpadr108\clcbpat23\cellx10368\pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\intbl\sb0\sa20{\loch
Do not run inside the ZIP: Always extract the installation ZIP first. Windows and Linux cannot reliably execute the apps while dependencies, databases, or shell scripts are still compressed.}\cell\row\pard \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80\loch

\par \pard\plain \s1\rtlch\af14\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af8\loch\keep\sb480\sa0\keepn\cf17\f8\fs32\b\dbch\af10{\loch
3. Pre-installation checklist}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
Choose the final TLOHome folder. Use a short absolute path such as C:\\TLOHome on Windows or $HOME/TLOHome on WSL/Linux.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
Confirm that TLOHome is writable by the account that will run the apps.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
Know how attached drives will be mounted. Windows runs can use drive-letter paths such as E:\\Music. WSL/Linux runs can use paths such as /mnt/e/Music after mountDrive.sh runs.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
Use visible and unique volume names for search roots. They are strongly recommended, especially with external drives, backup drives, WSL paths, or drives that may get different letters over time.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
If setlist.fm lookup will be used, obtain a setlist.fm API key and set SETLISTFM_API_KEY before enabling setlist.fm lookup.}
\par \trowd\trqc\ltrrow\trkeep\trpaddft3\trpaddt0\trpaddfl3\trpaddl0\trpaddfb3\trpaddb0\trpaddfr3\trpaddr0\clpadft3\clpadt108\clpadfr3\clpadr108\clcbpat23\cellx10368\pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\intbl\sb0\sa20{\loch
Installation contents: The installation ZIP installs the application files and support folders under TLOHome. Pre-installation setup is limited to choosing a writable TLOHome location, preparing environment variables, and making sure mounted drives will be visible.}\cell\row\pard \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80\loch

\par \pard\plain \s1\rtlch\af14\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af8\loch\keep\sb480\sa0\keepn\cf17\f8\fs32\b\dbch\af10{\loch
