\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033{\loch
TLO tracks inventory by visible volume name plus the path below the volume. It ignores and does not store the drive letter or WSL /mnt/<drive> prefix in bootlist.csv or the top SEARCH_PATH log headers. For example, [Backup-1]/mnt/e/Music and [Backup-1]/mnt/n/Music are treated as the same stored root [Backup-1] /Music when they refer to the same labeled volume.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
If no bracketed volume name is supplied, TLO substitutes the operating-system volume label for logging and existing-volume comparison when that label can be resolved. The default Windows-style labels New Volume and Local Disk are treated as blank rather than as useful volume names.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
If an explicit bracketed volume name is supplied, it must match the mounted drive label when that label can be resolved. A mismatch raises an alert and that path is not processed.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
For a labeled drive, TLO no longer asks whether to skip or re-inventory when it sees the same volume again. It applies the path relationship automatically: same path or parent path replaces that scope; child path replaces only entries below that child path; non-overlapping paths on the same volume are added to the same volume log header and appended.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
Explicit [] means an explicit blank volume. It is rejected when the mounted drive has a nonblank, non-default operating-system volume label.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
For drives with a blank volume label, or with the default labels New Volume or Local Disk, TLO uses one append-only blank-volume log set. The log header is SEARCH_PATH: [] with no path. There is no skip or re-inventory for blank/default-label drives, so you must avoid or clean up duplicates yourself if the same blank/default-label drive content is scanned multiple times.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
When more than one path is queued, TLO uses the resolved volume name to schedule the searches. All paths with a blank volume name form one group and run one at a time in drive-letter order. Each named volume forms its own group; several paths on the same named volume run one at a time inside that group so their shared logs remain safe. According to Performance Mode and Max Workers, the blank-volume group and different named-volume groups can run at the same time.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
A single labeled volume log can list multiple SEARCH_PATH header lines when you add non-overlapping roots from the same drive over time.}
\par \trowd\trqc\ltrrow\trkeep\trpaddft3\trpaddt0\trpaddfl3\trpaddl0\trpaddfb3\trpaddb0\trpaddfr3\trpaddr0\clpadft3\clpadt108\clpadfr3\clpadr108\clcbpat23\cellx10368\pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\intbl\sb0\sa20{\loch
Mount aliases: TLO rejects obvious duplicate and overlapping roots after normalization, but symlinks, junctions, case-sensitive aliases, and OS-specific mount aliases can still create duplicates if they point to the same content.}\cell\row\pard \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80\loch

\par \pard\plain \s2\rtlch\af14\afs26\ab \ltrch\hich\af8\loch\keep\sb200\sa0\keepn\cf18\f8\fs26\b\dbch\af10{\loch
Pre-run setup file: toBeInventoried.txt}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80{\loch
For full inventory runs, TLO uses TLOHome/toBeInventoried.txt unless a Search Path override is supplied in the GUI or with --search-path on the command line. Prepare this file before the run when you are not using a one-time Search Path override. Each non-comment line is one inventory root. Blank lines and lines whose first non-whitespace character is # are ignored. Lines beginning with REM are also treated as comments.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033{\loch
Windows root-path examples can be entered as E:, E:\\, or H:.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033{\loch
For WSL/Linux full inventory, Windows drive paths are translated to /mnt/<drive>/... while preserving the full subtree. Paths such as D:\\B-J\\D\\Dudek, Les are valid; the comma in the folder name is part of the path and should not cause TLO to scan only /mnt/d.}
\par \pard\plain \s81\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af9\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\li360\lin360\ri144\rin144\sb40\sa80\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f9\fs17\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af13\langfe1033\sb60\sa120{\loch
REM examples for Windows\line [External-E]E:\line [External-E]E:\\\line [Archive-H]H:\line [Backup-1]E:\\Music\line [Archive-F]F:\\boots --$slam "Bob Dylan"\line [Archive-G]G:\\incoming --$copy H:\\TaggedCopies\line [Archive-I]I:\\new --$copy-delete J:\\TaggedFinished --$slam "Bill Dickens"\line \line REM examples for WSL/Linux\line [Backup-1]/mnt/e/Music\line [Archive-F]/mnt/f/boots --$slam "Bob Dylan"\line [Archive-G]/mnt/g/incoming --$copy /mnt/h/TaggedCopies\line [Archive-I]/mnt/i/new --$copy-delete /mnt/j/TaggedFinished --$slam "Bill Dickens"}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
Optional per-path directives can be added after the path. Use --$slam ARTIST_NAME to force an artist, --$copy DESTINATION to copy and tag that path's folders at the destination, or --$copy-delete DESTINATION to copy/move, verify when needed, delete the original, and tag the transferred folders. Legacy -$slam still works.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
The order of --$slam and the copy directive does not matter, but a single line cannot contain both --$copy and --$copy-delete. Destination folders must already exist and must be fully qualified paths.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
Before inventory starts, TLO checks whether each copy destination has enough free space for the source root or roots assigned to it. If a destination is short on space, TLO stops and reports the destination, the affected source path or paths, and how much additional space is needed.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
When this capacity check is needed, the console first prints a Note explaining that TLO is checking source folder sizes before it checks destination capacity. Large roots can take a while to total, similar to opening folder Properties.}
\par \trowd\trqc\ltrrow\trkeep\trpaddft3\trpaddt0\trpaddfl3\trpaddl0\trpaddfb3\trpaddb0\trpaddfr3\trpaddr0\clpadft3\clpadt108\clpadfr3\clpadr108\clcbpat23\cellx10368\pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\intbl\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar{\loch
Volume label behavior: If no bracketed prefix is supplied, TLO uses the operating-system volume label for comparison and logging when available. Use [Volume] only when it matches the mounted drive label. Use [] only when an explicitly blank volume is intended and the mounted drive label is blank or unavailable.}\cell\row\pard \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80\loch

\par \pard\plain \s1\rtlch\af14\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af8\loch\keep\sb480\sa0\keepn\cf17\f8\fs32\b\dbch\af10{\loch
8. Running the main GUI}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80{\loch
Start the Windows GUI with TLOHome/apps/Windows/tlo-ggi.exe, or the WSL/Linux GUI from TLOHome/apps/Linux. The GUI can also be preloaded with command-line arguments such as --TLOHome, --search-path, --compliant, --compliant-artist-mode master|as-is, --etree-lookup, --setlistfm-lookup, --performance-mode, and --max-workers.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033{\loch
On native Windows installations, drag a folder from File Explorer and drop it onto the Search Path text box. The dropped folder replaces the Search Path value. If a file is dropped, TLO uses the containing folder.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033{\loch
The GUI and CLI share the same defaults through the internal option registry. setlist.fm still depends on etreeDB: command-line startup rejects --setlistfm-lookup unless --etree-lookup is also supplied, and the GUI automatically selects etreeDB when setlist.fm is selected.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033{\loch
When you click Inventory, the Inventory button should gray out immediately, the mutually exclusive Tag and Add Shows buttons should be disabled, and the output pane should show that the inventory request was accepted while TLO prepares the roots. If existing logs overlap the queued roots, TLO may show the Skip/Re-inventory prompt after this startup begins.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033{\loch
If you click Quit while a full inventory scan is active, TLO immediately warns that it will take a moment to clean up before exiting, then stops active workers and removes active run logs.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\qc\sb0\sa80{\loch
Figure 4. Main GUI controls. The same settings can be supplied on the command line when launching the GUI.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\rtlch\af14\afs26\ab \ltrch\hich\af8\loch\keep\sb200\sa0\keepn\cf18\f8\fs26\b\dbch\af10{\loch
Fields}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
Tag Copy/Delete Original -- Destination Path is a global full-inventory override. When filled, it overrides any per-path --$copy or --$copy-delete destination from toBeInventoried.txt. If Search Path is empty, TLO checks that this one destination can hold the combined source size of all accessible roots in toBeInventoried.txt before the run starts. During the run, TLO still reads the original folders for artist/date/show metadata, but successful copy/delete originals are inventoried at the destination.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
If the destination cannot hold the required source data, the GUI shows an alert naming the destination, the source path or paths, and the additional space needed.}
\par \trowd\trql\trleft5\ltrrow\trkeep\trpaddft3\trpaddt0\trpaddfl3\trpaddl0\trpaddfb3\trpaddb0\trpaddfr3\trpaddr0\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf1\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf1\clpadft3\clpadt108\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf1\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf1\clpadfr3\clpadr108\clcbpat24\cellx5184\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf1\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf1\clpadft3\clpadt108\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf1\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf1\clpadfr3\clpadr108\clcbpat24\cellx10362\pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\hyphpar0\f2\fs20\cf0\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af11\langfe1033\intbl\sl240\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa20{\rtlch\af14\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\langfe1033\loch
