Postprocess progress and timing: After the scan phase finishes, TLO may still need time to aggregate worker logs, export or reuse setlist files, write bootlist.csv, write unidentifiedShows.txt, and write summary.log. During this final stage, the console shows POSTPROCESS status lines and coarse setlist-export progress messages. The setlist progress messages are intentionally less frequent so large runs do not fill the console with repeated X/Y updates.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
If no source setlist exists, TLO creates a placeholder beginning with *** No setlist found ***, then available metadata, then recognized music filenames. Build 215 rescans the already-identified music folder for these filenames instead of relying on Phase 1 to log every media file.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
If a selected setlist contains the legacy message "Folder never contained an info file", TLO treats it as no usable setlist and creates the generated setlist from the folder's recognized music files.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
Generated setlist filenames preserve date dashes. Compact dates such as 19981003 normalize to 1998-10-03 before filename cleanup. Trailing parenthetical qualifiers are also preserved in exported setlist filenames, including source folder suffixes such as (SBD), (FM), (Volume 1), (Vol 2), and (v.3).}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
When a generated setlist filename already exists and the existing file size matches the size of the new setlist text, TLO assumes the files are identical and reuses the existing file instead of writing another copy.}
\par \pard\plain \s67\loch\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\loch\f4 \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360{\loch
When the filename exists but the file sizes differ, TLO writes an alternate setlist using a suffix such as (alt1) before .txt.}
