The numbered X in files such as compX.log or metaX.log identifies the tokenized log set. A full run can have more than one numbered set when multiple visible volumes are processed. One visible volume can also reuse a single token for multiple non-overlapping paths; those paths appear as multiple SEARCH_PATH lines at the top of the log. Exact or parent re-inventory truncates/replaces the affected token, child re-inventory prunes the child subtree and appends, and blank-label volumes always append to the single blank-volume token with SEARCH_PATH: [].}
